msg.content:
Here are the highest mountains in the five countries with the longest coastlines.

## Canada
The highest mountain in Canada is Mount Logan which is located in the Saint Elias Mountains and has an elevation of 5,959 metres.

## Norway
The highest mountain in Norway is Galdhøpiggen which has an elevation of 2,469 metres and is located in the Jotunheimen mountain region.

## Indonesia
The highest mountain in Indonesia is Puncak Jaya, which is located in the Sudirman Range in the central highlands of Papua.

## Russia
The highest mountain in Russia is Mount Elbrus, which has an elevation of 5,642 metres and is located in the Caucasus Mountains.

## Greenland
The highest mountain in Greenland is Gunnbjørn Fjeld which has an elevation of 3,694 metres and is located in the Watkins Range.
